.TH "_base_writeq" 9 "_base_writeq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_base_writeq \- 64 bit write to MMIO
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" _base_writeq
.BI "(__u64 b "  ","
.BI "volatile void __iomem *addr "  ","
.BI "spinlock_t *writeq_lock "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "b" 12
data payload
.IP "addr" 12
address in MMIO space
.IP "writeq_lock" 12
spin lock
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Glue for handling an atomic 64 bit word to MMIO. This special handling takes
care of 32 bit environment where its not quarenteed to send the entire word
in one transfer.
